<DOC><DOCNO> AP900402-0152 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-02-90 2202EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-Right-to-LifeRally     04-02 0114</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Right-to-Life Rally,110</SECOND><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Leaders of the National Right to LifeCommittee on Monday announced plans for an April 28 rally they arebilling as a ``celebration of life.''   ``We won't be marching or shouting,'' said John Willke,president of the group, which wants to outlaw abortion. ``What wewill be doing is celebrating, singing, speaking out and sharing ...the truth about abortion.''   The afternoon rally is to be held on the grounds of theWashington monument and will feature entertainment by musicians,Christian singers and celebrities.   Willke declined to estimate the size of the crowd he expects,but he said people from across the country are planning to attend.</TEXT></DOC>